The paper deals with learning human actions from video transcriptions, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach for weakly supervised learning, which involves machine learning (ML) techniques, making cs.LG a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on four distinct activity datasets, which involves multimedia (MM) techniques. Finally, the paper uses probabilistic models to infer actions within the video stream, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques.
